The paper deals with the recognition problem for simple-triangle graphs, which are intersection graphs of triangles defined by a point on a horizontal line and an interval on another horizontal line. This problem is related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG), as well as graph theory (cs.DS) and graph algorithms (cs.GT). The paper also mentions the 2-chain subgraph cover problem, which is a combinatorial optimization problem that falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
